{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox legislation | short_title = ''Jobs and Growth Act, 2012''<ref name=Legisinfo>{{cite web |url=http://www.parl.gc.ca/LegisInfo/BillDetails.aspx?Language=E&Mode=1&Bill=C45&Parl=41&Ses=1|author=Government of Canada |year=2012 |title=C-45: Status of the Bill |publisher=LEGISinfo |accessdate=January 16, 2013}}</ref> | caption = | long_title = ''A second Act to implement certain provisions of the budget tabled in Parliament on March 29, 2012 and other measures''<ref name=Legisinfo /> |alternativename=C-45 | citation = | enacted_by = | date_enacted = | date_assented = December 14, 2012<ref name=Legisinfo /> | date_signed = | date_commenced = | bill = | bill_citation = | bill_date = | introduced_by = [[Jim Flaherty]], [[Minister of Finance]]<ref name=Legisinfo /> | 1st_reading = October 18, 2012<ref name=Legisinfo /> | 2nd_reading = October 31, 2012<ref name=Legisinfo /> | 3rd_reading = December 5, 2012<ref name=Legisinfo /> | white_paper = | committee_report = November 26, 2012<ref name=Legisinfo /> | amendments = | related = | summary = }} {{Italic title}} The '''''Jobs and Growth Act, 2012'''''<ref>[http://www.parl.gc.ca/content/hoc/Bills/411/Government/C-45/C-45_4/C-45_4.PDF ''Jobs and Growth Act, 2012'', S.C. 2012, c. 31]</ref> (informally referred to as '''Bill C-45''') (the ''Act'') is an Act of the [[Parliament of Canada]]. It was passed in December 2012 from the second [[omnibus bill]] introduced by the Conservative government to implement its 2012 budget,<ref>{{cite web |title=Bill C-45: What's In Omnibus Budget Bill 2? |date=January 18, 2013 |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/10/18/bill-c-45-omnibus-budget-bill_n_1981967.html |website=Huffington Post |accessdate=January 18, 2013}}</ref> following the passage of the ''[[Jobs, Growth and Long-term Prosperity Act]]'' in June 2012.<ref>[http://www.parl.gc.ca/content/hoc/Bills/411/Government/C-38/C-38_4/C-38_4.PDF ''Jobs, Growth and Long-term Prosperity Act'', S.C. 2012, c. 19]</ref> Both bills attracted controversy both for their size (>450 pages each) and for the breadth of provisions contained that were not fiscally related.
==Content of the ''Act''==
